        "answer_count": 0,
        "title": "How slf4j+log4j application resumes work When the hard disk is full",
        "body": "<p>I used the logging system in a web application.The log system is <code>slf4j + log4j<\/code>.  <\/p>\n\n<p>The configuration file is as follows.  <\/p>\n\n<p>Now I have a problem.  <\/p>\n\n<p>In the first step, I used a pressure test program. Unfortunately, the hard disk was filled and the log could not be output.   <\/p>\n\n<p>In the second step, I deleted the extra logs and the hard disk regained space. Unfortunately, my log system could not continue working.<\/p>\n\n<p>I had to restart my service to recover the log system. <\/p>\n\n<p>This is obviously not the best solution. How can I get the logs to work again?<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;\n&lt;configuration scan=\"true\" scanPeriod=\"60 seconds\" debug=\"false\"&gt;\n    &lt;property name=\"LOG_ROOT\" value=\"logs/\"/&gt;\n    &lt;property name=\"SVC_NAME\" value=\"robot-test\"/&gt;\n\n    &lt;appender name=\"AllLog\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.RollingFileAppender\"&gt;\n        &lt;rollingPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.TimeBasedRollingPolicy\"&gt;\n            &lt;fileNamePattern&gt;${LOG_ROOT}${HOSTNAME}.${SVC_NAME}.%d{yyyy-MM-dd-HH}.log&lt;/fileNamePattern&gt;\n        &lt;/rollingPolicy&gt;\n\n        &lt;!--&lt;rollingPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.TimeBasedRollingPolicy\"&gt;--&gt;\n            &lt;!--&lt;fileNamePattern&gt;${LOG_ROOT}${HOSTNAME}.${SVC_NAME}.%d{yyyy-MM-dd-HH}-%i.log&lt;/fileNamePattern&gt;--&gt;\n            &lt;!--&lt;MaxHistory&gt;30&lt;/MaxHistory&gt;--&gt;\n            &lt;!--&lt;timeBasedFileNamingAndTriggeringPolicy class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.rolling.SizeAndTimeBasedFNATP\"&gt;--&gt;\n                &lt;!--&lt;maxFileSize&gt;100MB&lt;/maxFileSize&gt;--&gt;\n            &lt;!--&lt;/timeBasedFileNamingAndTriggeringPolicy&gt;--&gt;\n        &lt;!--&lt;/rollingPolicy&gt;--&gt;\n\n\n        &lt;encoder charset=\"UTF8\"&gt;\n            &lt;pattern&gt;%d{HH:mm:ss.SSS} %level [%thread] %logger{10} [%file:%line] %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;\n        &lt;/encoder&gt;\n    &lt;/appender&gt;\n\n    &lt;appender name=\"STDOUT\" class=\"ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender\"&gt;\n        &lt;filter class=\"ch.qos.logback.classic.filter.ThresholdFilter\"&gt;\n            &lt;level&gt;${logging.stdout.appender.level}&lt;/level&gt;\n        &lt;/filter&gt;\n        &lt;encoder charset=\"UTF8\"&gt;\n            &lt;pattern&gt;%date %level [%thread] %logger{10} [%file:%line] %msg%n&lt;/pattern&gt;\n        &lt;/encoder&gt;\n    &lt;/appender&gt;\n\n    &lt;logger name=\"com.smzy.commonservice\" level=\"WARN\" addtivity=\"false\"/&gt;\n\n    &lt;root level=\"${logging.root.level}\"&gt;\n        &lt;appender-ref ref=\"AllLog\"/&gt;\n        &lt;appender-ref ref=\"STDOUT\"/&gt;\n    &lt;/root&gt;\n&lt;/configuration&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
